Program: Free Thinking
Title: Landmark - This Sporting Life
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b09j0rt6
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 12 Dec 2017
Philip Dodd discusses the significance of David Storey's groundbreaking 1960 novel with social historian Juliet Gardiner, journalist Rod Liddle, writer Anthony Clavane and the author's daughter Kate Storey. Producer: Torquil MacLeod.